snippet.title: Best Practices for Setting up a large NodeJS Project
snippet.description: In this video we will take a look at the best practices we can and should follow when setting up a mid to large project using NodeJS.

snippet.title: Designing a clean REST API with Node.js (Express + Mongo)
snippet.description:
We walk through the code of a REST API written in Node.js with Mongo and Express.js and talk about some design decisions and the application of several Architecture Principles including Separation of Concerns, designing for change, and more...

source code: https://github.com/arcdev1/mm_express_api_example

snippet.title: Late Night Docker: AMA Node.js Dockerfile Best Practices
snippet.description:
This video walks through a Node.js sample project for how to get the best out of Docker when doing node development. 

Late Night Docker is a YouTube Live series I'm doing on common Docker topics, unscripted and unedited.

This edition includes a Docker FAQ on Dockerfiles, Compose files, debugging, nodemon, npm package management, and more for Node.js. I recorded this to be edited down later, but thought a YouTube Live would be handy for those needing a better Node experience with Docker for development.

Sample Project: https://github.com/BretFisher/node-docker-good-defaults

Origional AMA: https://github.com/BretFisher/ama/issues/2

My Docker Newsletter, Udemy Course Coupons, and More: https://www.bretfisher.com
